  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On pages 1-2 of this manuscript, there is a letter from James Miller M&apos;Kim to Wendell Phillips. M&apos;Kim asks Wendell Phillips to deliver to Mrs. Maria Weston Chapman a Bible and a prayer book &quot;containing as a frontispiece, Schaeffers [sic] picture of Christ the Consoler,&quot; with the black man left out. These books are for the southern trade.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On pages 2-3 of this manuscript, there is a separate note by James Miller M&apos;Kim presumably to Maria Weston Chapman. M&apos;Kim asks Maria W. Chapman if she intends to send the Bible and prayer book (described in the previous letter) to Mr. Ary Scheffer. M&apos;Kim knows the publisher Lippincott personally, and he knows the artist who engraved the picture.</subfield>
  </datafield>
